race.comment: LAZZURA (1) proven Group winning mare who returns with excellent fresh credentials. Can sit off this lot and round them up effortlessly with the two trials under the belt. The one to beat. CINSAULT (8) building a good winning CV this time in and keeps raising the bar. No surprise to see her get some black type on her record after producing good figures at the last two wins. Maps well and shapes as a leading chance. MARETH (11) nice filly who returns from a let-up after going under narrowly when second in the LR Gosford Guineas over 1200m. Kept up to the mark when fourth in a 902m trial. Adept in all conditions and Lloyd retains the ride. DARK GLITTER (5) on the quick backup after surging late along the inside with an unlucky fourth in the G3 Triscay over 1200m at Randwick last Saturday. Ran second in this race last year and not to be overlooked. PINITO (4) Queensland Oaks runner-up resuming. Can pull out a big run fresh and sneak into the minor money.
